<title>UK: Laporte sells businesses for 7.8 mln stg.</title>
<headline>Laporte sells businesses for 7.8 mln stg.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Specialty chemcicals group Laporte Plc said on Monday it has sold a number of non-core businesses for a total of 7.8 million stg, resulting in a goodwill right-off of around 5 million stg.  </p>
<p>In a statement, Laporte said it sold businesses in Thailand and France, and all of its remaining operations in Brazil.</p>
<p>The sales mean the disposal program announced earlier this year as part of a major restructuring is now almost complete, with around 20 million stg of businesses remaining to be sold.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
